We will remain committed to security in Afghanistan in the post-2014 period.
Today, almost 40 percent of goods that are not destructive are transported to Afghanistan through Azerbaijan.
The route from Azerbaijan is the safest and safest route.
We will continue our efforts to promote peace and stability in our region.
At the same time, we also took part in peacekeeping operations in Kosovo in the past.
Our participation in NATO's peacekeeping operations is an important part of our cooperation.
We are cooperating in the fight against terrorism. Our Armed Forces are adapted to NATO standards.
I am grateful for NATO's support for the reforms in our Armed Forces.
We also carry out mine clearance projects in Azerbaijan with NATO assistance, including financial support.
At the same time, Azerbaijan contributes to the Trust Fund of the Afghan National Army.
We have already provided financial assistance of 1 million euros and we will provide 1 million euros more.
Today, I would like to add that we will add an additional 1 million euros to the Trust Fund of the Afghan National Army.
We value this step as a contribution to peace and security in Afghanistan.
